&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looking for a role where your attention to detail can make a real impact? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Join a well-established health fund organisation that genuinely values its people. With a supportive and welcoming team, a strong focus on employee wellbeing, and opportunities to learn and grow, you&#39;ll be part of a workplace where your contributions are recognised and your career can thrive.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;If you&#39;re an organised administrator who enjoys learning new systems, working in a collaborative environment and delivering accurate work, we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12-month ongoing contract with the opportunity to become permanent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid working model after training (3 days WFH, 2 days in the Parramatta office)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$34.38 per hour + super&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive 4-week onsite training program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monday to Friday office hours - no weekend work!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modern office based in Parramatta&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health and wellbeing initiatives that support work-life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A fun and engaging workplace with an active social calendar, including team events, cook-off competitions and other activities throughout the year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Next Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;We&#39;re looking for an&lt;strong&gt; Administration officer &lt;/strong&gt;to join the team in a varied role where no two days are exactly the same. You&#39;ll review member information, assess refund eligibility and process requests accurately, ensuring every case is handled with care and attention to detail.&lt;br&gt;Working across multiple systems, you&#39;ll play an important role in keeping records up to date and supporting a high standard of service for members. While the role is predominantly administration-focused, you&#39;ll also assist members with occasional phone enquiries.&lt;br&gt;If you enjoy structured work, take pride in accuracy and are adaptable to changing priorities, this could be the perfect opportunity.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review member information and assess refund eligibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process member requests accurately while maintaining detailed records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work across multiple systems, including Microsoft Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to occasional member enquiries via phone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all work is completed in line with company procedures and quality standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with colleagues to support the day-to-day operations of the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage competing priorities while maintaining a high level of accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous administration experience in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidence using multiple computer systems and Microsoft Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent attention to detail and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organisational skills with the ability to prioritise competing tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
